- Documentation
    - Write README - Document exact behaviour (how timestamp-less lines combined together and sorted first etc)
- Usability
    - Support: Included / excluded paths
    - Support CLI flags for all customizations. CLI flags will be more prioritized than config file.
- Code tidy up
    - Aggressively simplify the code so we can easily implement advanced algorithms and features in the future.
    - Add method comments
    - Use named return values to document code better and enjoy better autocomplete.
- Other
    - Define install recipe in justfile to install the binary to the system (and uninstall maybe)
    - Decide a standard naming for binaries across all projects - Research
    - Complete unit tests
    - Allow breaking strict line ordering in favor of keeping logs from same source together, like up to a certain threshold (not exceeding 1sec for example)
    - Add unified log level support to format output logs in IDE better (print log level just like timestamp)
    - Support merging log files from withing archive files (zip, tar etc)

- Customizations
  - Support: Multiple input paths
  - Support: Dry-run
  - Support: Including / excluding symlinks
  - Support: Opt in to add standardized log level to the output
  - Support: Opt in to remove timestamp from raw line
  - Support: Opt in to remove log level from raw line
  - Support: Custom source name format
  - Support: Custom timestamp format
  - Support: Default local timezone if no timezone information in the timestamp
- Performance
  - Consider adaptive sorting like Timsort just like 'sort' command in Unix.
    Depending on input size and distribution, tools dynamically choose between sorting algorithms
    like quicksort, mergesort, or insertion sort.
  - Experiment splitting files into chunks and sorting and merging in multiple steps.
  - Read files concurrently -> Fill the read buffer while other parts of the program are processing the lines.
  - Take max open file descriptor limit into account. If there are too many files, we couldn't open all of them simultaneously.
    Consider using temporary intermediate files to store the sorted lines and merge them later using efficient algorithms
    like merge sort.
  - Create an alternative solution with sort and awk to compare performance.
  - Implement an alternative in Rust.
  - 'sort' and 'awk': Algorithms are optimized for CPU cache by working on small, contiguous chunks of data that fit in the L1/L2 cache.
